This is the dessert that we serve when we need something tasty and don't have much time. It is so easy and everyone comments on how good it tastes. I am taking it to supper club tonight for someone that can't eat wheat.

Rating: 4
Delicious! I only made 2 changes: soaking about 1 cup of dried cherries in the kirsch, simmering them till soft...and leaving out the cornstarch. Instead, I reduced the whole thing which takes more time, but I do so hate the taste of cornstarch! This is unbelievable with the ice cream, and it's even better if you slip a nice fudgy brownie into the microwave for a couple of seconds and then proceed...

